	"description": "There’s nothing as flashy and useful for JavaScript interviews than recursion.\n\nIf you just want to be impressive with recursion in JavaScript, here are some\nsemi real-world (technical test type) examples.\n\nThe short definition of a recursive solution to a problem (in computer science)\nis: don’t use iteration. This usually means a function has to call itself with a\nsmaller instance of the same problem. It does this until it hits a trivial case\n(usually defined in the problem).\n\nHence, recursion ",
